content.title: Microsoft Graph throttling guidance
content.content: The Microsoft Graph service implements throttling limits to ensure service availability and reliability. Throttling limits vary based on the scenario. For example, if you're performing a large volume of writes, the possibility for throttling is higher than if you're only performing reads.
